    {
      "id": "cbacbf4b-11c7-4876-9696-a6cf8b73bd97",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Abstract starts with distinction between EDM and LA, arguing that the former is a lot more automated while the second is more “domain knowledge” driven. Then, the authors go into the task of generating pre-requisite rules from a set of online educational resources. In essence, the authors aim to automate the process of figuring out what pre-requisites should a student have before studying some materials.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
